

shell> ./Linux-i686/bin/test_binary_serialization

shell> od -t u1 test_binary_serialization.data 
0000000 127   7   0   0   0   0   1  42   2 154   2   4   0 225 245   5
0000020   4 255 255 255 255 255 255   1   4 116 111 116 111
0000035


where 127== 'e'|'o'|'s'
7 0 0 0 == 32 bits for library version

0    -> integer==0
1 42 -> integer==42 (1 byte is enough) 
2 154 2 -> integer==666 (2 bytes are enough) 
4   0 225 245   5 -> integer==100000000 (needs 4 bytes)
4 255 255 255 25 -> integer==0xFFFFFFF (needs 4 bytes)
255 255 -> size == -1 -> negative number == -1
1 4 -> integer==4 (1 byte is enough) this is the size of a string
116 111 116 111 -> 4 ASCII codes for the "toto" string

